1. Introduction
The Mobile Recharge Shop Management System is a console-based Java application developed using Object-Oriented Programming (OOP).
It helps a mobile recharge shop manage customers, recharge plans, payments, and recharge history.
The system provides a simple and organized way to perform mobile recharges efficiently.

2. Problem Statement

Many small recharge shops manually record customer details and recharge information,
which can lead to errors, duplicate records, and difficulty in tracking transactions.
This project automates the recharge process using Java.

3.OOP Concepts Used
Encapsulation

Customer and RechargePlan classes keep data private using private variables and provide public getter methods.

Inheritance

A PremiumCustomer class can extend the Customer class to provide special offers.

Polymorphism

Different payment methods like UPI, Card, or Cash can override the pay() method.

Abstraction

A Payment interface or abstract class can define a common payment method for all payment types.